The paper deals with a distributed setting where independent samples are distributed across multiple players, and communication constraints are imposed on the players. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Distributed Systems (cs.DS) categories. The paper also focuses on inference problems, which suggests that it may belong to the Learning (cs.LG) or Computational Complexity (cs.CC) categories. Finally, the paper proposes a general formulation for inference problems in the distributed setting, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category.
